title: Libya Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Libya increased 3.91 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Libya averaged 9.90 percent from 2005 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 52.64 percent in December of 2017 and a record low of -12.12 percent in October of 2012. This page provides - Libya Food Inflation - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bureau of Statistics and Census Libya
